    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>European daggers with light blades, square or triangular in section, and a reinforced beadlike point, in use primarily during the 16th and 17th centuries as parrying daggers in swordplay.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
